    <p align="left" class="style12">Jr. Facilities Modifications/Coordinator</p>
    
    <p align="left"><br />
      As a leading partner with the Lone Star Unmanned Aircraft Systems Center of Excellence and Innovation (LSUASC), a UAS test site for the Federal Aviation Administration, we are seeking a Jr. Facilities Modifications/Coordinator to join the LSUASC team of top-flight engineers and other professionals focused on innovative solutions for the purpose of integrating UAS into the national airspace.</p>
    <p align="left"><br />
      <strong>Description:</strong><br />
      Participates in all phases of the development to assure that technical and programmatic needs are understood and given appropriate priority. May assist team leads in program planning, and scheduling of project &amp; assets to accomplish technical and programmatic objectives. This includes, project planning/status, configuration management, asset scheduling, cost effects and control, quality assurance and program audits. Also included is the test planning, preparation, conduct and data regression analysis both from a technical and programmatic standpoint. Understands engineering product/services and how they relate to program goals and objectives. Also maintains knowledge in test planning, asset scheduling, safety, environmental, information technology or other related high technology fields.</p>
    <p align="left"><strong><br />
      Job Responsibilities include:</strong><br />
       Coordinates facilities modifications and provides oversight for all IT and Facilities construction<br />
       Experience in construction required specifically with the State of Texas and according to TAMUS rules</p>
    <p align="left"><strong><br />
      Basic Qualifications:</strong><br />
       No degree with 9 years of job related experience or Associates Degree with 7 years of related experience or a Bachelor’s Degree in technical or management field with 5 years of related experience<br />
       Strong administrative skills and background<br />
       Strong communication and interpersonal skills<br />
       U.S. Citizenship required</p>
    <p align="left"><br />
      <strong>Work Location:</strong> Corpus Christi, Texas<br />
      Relocation assistance may be available<br />
      Applicants selected may be subject to a background investigation<br />
    </p>
    <p align="left" class="style22"><strong><br />
      Jr. HAZMAT and Materials Specialist</strong></p>
    <p align="left"><br />
